      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Here are the results for your query:\n\n## **\"Emergent World Representations: Exploring a Sequence Model Trained on a Synthetic Task\"**\n\nThis is a paper by "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Kenneth Li, Aspen K. Hopkins, David Bau, Fernanda B. Viégas, Hanspeter Pfister, and Martin Wattenberg"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "presented at The Eleventh International Conference on Learning Representations (ICLR 2023), held in Kigali, Rwanda, May 1-5, 2023"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": ". It was presented as an **oral** at the conference.\n\n### Summary\n\nThe paper asks whether sequence models merely memorize surface statistics or develop internal world models. "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The authors investigate this question by applying a variant of the GPT model to the task of predicting legal moves in a simple board game, Othello."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Although the network has no a priori knowledge of the game or its rules, they uncover evidence of an emergent nonlinear internal representation of the board state."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Interventional experiments indicate this representation can be used to control the output of the network and create \"latent saliency maps\" that can help explain predictions in human terms."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n### Key Contributions\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The paper presents four contributions: (1) evidence for an emergent world model in a GPT variant trained to produce legal moves in Othello; (2) a comparison of linear and non-linear probing approaches, finding that non-linear probes are superior in this context; (3) an intervention technique suggesting that the emergent world model can be used to control the network's behavior; and (4) showing how probes can be used to produce latent saliency maps."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n### Key Links\n\n- **arXiv**: https://arxiv.org/abs/2210.13382\n- **OpenReview**: https://openreview.net/forum?id=DeG07_TcZvT\n- **Code**: "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The official GitHub repository is at `likenneth/othello_world`, with implementation based on minGPT by Andrej Karpathy."
      }
